-- Negative EPS Surprises for First Quarter of ’13 for S&P 500
-- B y   W e n d y   S o o n g
-- 2013-06-12T20:37:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-12/negative-eps-surprises-for-first-quarter-of-13-for-s-p-500.html
Following are negative earnings surprises
for the first quarter of 2013 for companies in the  Standard & Poor’s (SPX) 
500 Index. So far, 24.2 percent (120 out of 496) of the  S&P 500  have
reported negative surprises.  The median for negative earnings surprises is -6.5 percent and the
fourth-spread average is -6.2 percent. A fourth-spread average is the
average unaffected by observations in the smallest 25 percent or the
largest 25 percent of the data.  This list ranks percent surprises of  actual earnings  to earnings
estimates for the quarter. Profit figures are based on income from
continuing operations excluding some gains and losses.  Earnings estimates 
are provided by Bloomberg.  
